CodeList.Name: Neoplasm Type

Description.TranslatedText: The terminology that includes concepts relevant to benign or malignant tissue growth.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A low-grade malignant neoplasm composed of epithelial cells and a spindle cell osteo-fibrous proliferation.
A malignant neoplasm arising from glandular cells that includes focal or extensive areas of squamous metaplasia.
A malignant neoplasm comprising glandular epithelial clear cells.
A malignant glandular neoplasm of the uterine lining.
A malignant neoplasm arising from glandular cells.
An adenocarcinoma comprising neoplastic glandular cells containing intracytoplasmic mucin.
An adenocarcinoma with papillary growth pattern.
An adenocarcinoma with sebaceous differentiation.
Benign mixed neoplasm comprised of epithelial/glandular and mesenchymal structures.
Benign mixed neoplasm comprised of epithelial/glandular and lipomatous structures.
A benign glandular epithelial neoplasm comprising secretory cells forming acinar patterns.
A benign glandular epithelial neoplasm comprising secretory cells forming acinar patterns.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: BENIGN ADENOMA OF THE ADRENAL GLAND
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A benign neoplasm arising from any of the adrenal cortical layers.

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: ADENOMA, ANTERIOR LOBE PITUITARY GLAND, BENIGN
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A benign neoplasm of the anterior lobe of the pituitary gland.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: BASAL CELL ADENOMA OF SALIVARY GLAND
BASAL CELL ADENOMA OF THE SALIVARY GLAND

A benign neoplasm arising from epithelium.
A benign neoplasia of the lung, arising from bronchial epithelium.
A benign lung neoplasm arising from the alveolar/bronchiolar epithelium.
A benign neoplasm arising from C-cells of the thyroid gland.

CERUMINOUS ADENOMA OF THE EXTERNAL AUDITORY CANAL

A benign neoplasm comprising glands containing epithelial clear cells.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: FOLLICULAR ADENOMA OF THE THYROID GLAND

A benign epithelial neoplasm arising from hepatocytes.
A benign neoplasm arising from the intrahepatic bile duct.
A benign neoplasm arising from the islet cells of the pancreas.
A benign epithelial neoplasm of the thyroid gland comprising follicular cells with cytoplasmic clearing.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A benign, cystic epithelial neoplasm comprising cells containing intracytoplasmic mucin.
A benign epithelial neoplasm characterized by the presence of papillary epithelial patterns.
A benign epithelial neoplasm arising from the pars distalis of the anterior pituitary gland.
A benign epithelial neoplasm arising from the pars intermedia of the anterior pituitary gland.
A benign neoplasm of the pituitary gland.
A benign neoplasm arising from the renal cortex.
A benign epithelial neoplasm arising from the rete testis.
A benign neoplasm arising from sebaceous glands.
A benign tubular adenoma with Sertoli cell differentiation.
A benign epithelias neoplasm arising from sweat glands.
A benign neoplasm arising from glandular epithelium, characterized by a tubular architectural pattern.
A benign ovarian epithelial neoplasm characterized by the presence of tubular structures and interstitial stroma.
A benign epithelial neoplasm arising from the yolk sac.
A benign neoplasm of the rodent Zymbal's gland with sebaceous and/or squamous differentiation.
A benign neoplasm characterized by the presence of a glandular and a mesenchymal component.
A benign neoplasm located beneath the adrenal capsule.
A malignant neoplasm located beneath the adrenal capsule.
A neoplasm located beneath the adrenal capsule in which the malignancy status has not been established.
A neoplasm of the adrenal cortex in which the malignancy status has not been established.
A benign odontogenic neoplasm arising from the epithelial component of the embryonic tooth.
A malignant odontogenic neoplasm arising from the epithelial component of the embryonic tooth.
A odontogenic neoplasm arising from the epithelial component of the embryonic tooth of undetermined malignancy status.

A lipoma characterized by prominent vascularization.

A benign neoplasm of the brain or spinal cord arising from astrocytes associated with single or multiple cysts.
A neoplasm of the brain or spinal cord exhibiting astrocytic differentiation, but in which the malignancy status has not been established.
A benign papillary neoplasm of the skin.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: SKIN MIXED BASAL AND SQUAMOUS CELL CARCINOMA
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A basal cell carcinoma (skin neoplasm) which displays squamous differentiation.

A malignant epithelial neoplasm of the anterior pituitary gland in which the neoplastic cells stain positive with acidic dyes.
A malignant glandular epithelial neoplasm comprising secretory cells forming acinar patterns.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: MIXED ADENOCARCINOMA AND EPIDERMOID CELL CARCINOMA
MIXED ADENOCARCINOMA AND SQUAMOUS CELL CARCINOMA

A malignant epithelial neoplasm arising from sebaceous or sweat glands or from hair follicles.
A malignant epithelial neoplasm arising from adrenal cortical cells.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: BASAL CELL CARCINOMA OF THE SKIN
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A malignant epithelial neoplasm arising from basal cells of the epidermis and pilosebaceous unit of skin [the dermis].
A malignant neoplasia of the lung, arising from bronchial epithelium.
A malignant lung neoplasm originating from the alveolar/bronchiolar epithelium.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: MEDULLARY CARCINOMA OF THE THYROID GLAND
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A neuroendocrine malignant epithelial neoplasm arising from C-cells of the thyroid gland.
A malignant neoplasm derived from ceruminous glands in the external auditory canal.
A malignant neoplasm arising from the choroid plexus of the brain.
A non-seminomatous malignant germ cell neoplasm of the testis or ovary.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: FOLLICULAR CARCINOMA OF THE THYROID GLAND
FOLLICULAR CANCER OF THE THYROID GLAND
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A malignant neoplasia arising from follicular cells of the thyroid gland.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: PRIMARY CARCINOMA OF THE LIVER CELLS
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A malignant neoplasm arising from hepatocytes.
A malignant neoplasm of the liver containing unequivocal elements of both hepatocellular and cholangiocarcinoma intimately admixed.
A malignant epithelial neoplasm confined to the epithelial layer and without evidence of further tissue invasion.
A malignant endocrine neoplasm arising from islets of Langerhans of the pancreas.
A malignant epithelial neoplasm.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A malignant neuroendocrine neoplasm comprising cells containing secretory granules.
A malignant epithelial neoplasm arising from the pars distalis of the pituitary gland.
A malignant epithelial neoplasm arising from the pars intermedia of the pituitary gland.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: MUCINOUS TUBULAR AND SPINDLE CELL CARCINOMA OF THE KIDNEY
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A malignant neoplasm of the kidney, characterized by the presence of tubules.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Mucinous Tubular and Spindle Cell Carcinoma of the Kidney

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A malignant epithelial neoplasm characterized by the presence of spindle cells.

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: CARCINOMA, SQUAMOUS CELL, IN SITU, MALIGNANT

A malignant neoplasm arising from squamous epithelial cells.
A malignant neoplasm arising from sweat glands.

A malignant glandular neoplasm exhibiting tubular structures.
A malignant epithelial neoplasm of the ovary with tubular and stromal neoplastic components.
A malignant epithelial neoplasm exhibiting poor differentiation (anaplasia).
A malignant neoplasm of the rodent Zymbal's gland with sebaceous and/or squamous differentiation.
A malignant neoplasm comprising a mixture of carcinomatous and sarcomatous elements.
A benign neoplasm of the chemoreceptor system (e.g. carotid body, glomus jugulare, glomus vagale).

A neoplasm of the chemoreceptor system (e.g. carotid body, glomus jugulare, glomus vagale) for which the malignancy status has not be established.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: INTRAHEPATIC CARCINOMA OF THE BILE DUCT
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A malignant neoplasm of the liver arising from/comprising cells resembling those of bile ducts.
A malignant neoplasm arising from/comprising cells resembling those of bile ducts.
A benign neoplasm arising from/comprising cells resembling those of bile ducts.

A neoplasm of ependymal origin, for which the malignancy status has not been established.
A benign neoplasm arising from epithelial cells of the skin.

A malignant mesenchymal neoplasm of the soft tissue and bone.

A neoplasm of bone comprised of giant cells (osteoclast-like) and mononuclear cells, for which the malignancy status has not been established.

A neoplasm originating from vascular pericytes (cells in the periphery of vessels), for which the malignancy status has not been established.

A benign neoplasm of the brown adipose tissue.

A malignant neoplasm composed of adipose tissue.

A malignant neoplasm composed of immunoblasts (large B cells).
A malignant neoplasm composed of lymphoblasts (lymphoid precursor cells).

A benign neoplasm composed of mast cells.

A general term used to describe autonomous growth of tissue where the originating cell type has not been characterized. The term benign indicates the absence of morphologic features associated with malignancy (for instance severe atypia, nuclear pleomorphism, tumor cell necrosis, and abnormal mitoses).

A neoplasm composed of cells of neuroendocrine origin for which the malignancy status has not been established.

PRIMITIVE NEUROECTODERMAL NEOPLASM OF THE PINEAL GLAND

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: A poorly differentiated malignant embryonal neoplasm arising from the pineal region of the brain.
A benign neoplasm of the brain arising from the pineal gland.
A neoplasm arising from the posterior lobe of the pituitary gland.
A malignant neoplasm composed of plasma cells.
A neoplasm, originating from glandular epithelium, exhibiting polypoid growth, for which the malignancy status has not been determined.
A benign polypoid neoplasm of the endometrium projecting into the endometrial cavity.
